description.narrative: The Project Development Objective is to increase crop yields and cropping intensity in the selected existing irrigation sites in the Recipient's Bago East, Nay Pyi Taw, Mandalay, and Sagaing regions, and, in the event of an Eligible Crisis or Emergency, to provide immediate and effective response to said Eligible Crisis or Emergency.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Annual Work Plans and Budgets | Description :Obligation of the Recipient to prepare and submit for approval byIDA detailed annual work plans and budgets for all Project activities. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Contingent Emergency Response | Description :Obligation of the Recipient to adopt a satisfactory ContingentEmergency Response Implementation Plan for the Component 4 of the Project and, in the event of an eligible crisis or emergency,ensure that the activities under said component are carried out in accordance with such plan and all relevant safeguardrequirements. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Environmental and Social Safeguards | Description :Obligation of the Recipient to carry out the Project inaccordance with the Environmental and Social Framework Management (ESMF) and all safeguard provisions of the legal agreement,including the preparation and implementation of all site-specific safeguard assessments and plans required under the ESMF. |Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Institutional arrangements | Description :Obligation of the Recipient to maintain, at all times during theimplementation of the Project, the Project Steering Committee, the Project Management Unit, and the Agricultural CoordinationCommittees in participating townships and districts. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
Finance Agreement :Project Operational Manual | Description :Obligation of the Recipient to carry out the Project in accordancewith the Project Implementation Manual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
